                "content": "Seen this movie before. A QoQ dip on prime doesn\u2019t define the whole market. Marina/JVC leasing is still sticky \u2014 good units rent fast, renewals are coming in at the RERA-guided caps, and quality tenants stay when you maintain and price correctly. Volumes cooling after a hot run (plus seasonality) is normal.\n\nI\u2019m a long-term holder: focus on cash flow, low leverage, and steady occupancy. I\u2019ll raise rents where the index allows and the market supports, not because of headlines. 2009/2015/2020 taught me corrections are healthy and usually separate speculators from operators. Let\u2019s see 2\u20133 quarters of data before calling a downturn.",
